## **PART 4: CONCEPT MATCHING (Stage 3 - Landing Page Optimization)**

### **Step 4.1: Identify Top Performing TAM × UMOP Combinations**

**What it is:** Look at your cumulative data from Stage 1 + Stage 2 and identify which TAM × UMOP combinations are driving the most conversions.

**Analysis:**

Look at performance by **concept** (not just individual ad):

**Example results:**

| Concept (TAM × UMOP) | Total Spend | Total Conv | Avg CPA | Winner? |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Dads + Can't keep up with kids | $1,200 | 42 | $29 | ✅ #1 |
| Lifters + Wife hates belly | $890 | 28 | $32 | ✅ #2 |
| Professionals + Health markers | $780 | 19 | $41 | ✅ #3 |
| Dads + Wife hates belly | $650 | 12 | $54 | ⚠️ OK |
| Ex-athletes + Performance | $420 | 6 | $70 | ❌ Weak |

**Key insight:**
"Dads + Can't keep up with kids" is the DOMINANT winner across formats and awareness stages.

**Output:** Ranked list of top 2-3 TAM × UMOP combinations

---

### **Step 4.2: Clone and Customize Landing Pages**

**What it is:** Create landing page variants matched to your top-performing TAM × UMOP combinations.

**Why this matters:**
- Message match from ad → landing page increases conversion rate
- Same generic landing page for all traffic = leaving money on table
- Personalization increases trust and reduces friction

**How to do it:**

**Step 1: Duplicate your existing landing page**
- Use your landing page builder (Unbounce, Leadpages, Webflow, etc.)
- Create 2-3 copies

**Step 2: Customize each copy for the specific TAM × UMOP**

**Elements to change:**

**Headline:**
- Generic: "Lose Your Beer Belly in 30 Days"
- Matched: "Dads: Get Your Energy Back and Keep Up With Your Kids"

**Subheadline:**
- Generic: "Our proven system targets visceral fat"
- Matched: "You can't dad-mode on low energy. Target the hormonal cause of belly fat—without killing your strength or energy."

**Hero image/video:**
- Generic: Product shot
- Matched: Dad playing with kids, before/after of a dad, testimonial from a dad

**Social proof:**
- Generic: "5,000 customers"
- Matched: "1,200+ dads got their energy back"

**Testimonials:**
- Generic: Mix of everyone
- Matched: Only dad testimonials, specifically mentioning kid-related wins

**CTA:**
- Generic: "Buy Now"
- Matched: "Get Your Energy Back - 30 Day Guarantee"

**Body copy:**
- Use the TAM's language
- Reference the UMOP throughout
- Tell stories relevant to that TAM

**Example comparison:**

**Generic landing page:**
```
Headline: Lose Your Beer Belly Fast
Subhead: Our proven formula targets stubborn belly fat
Hero: Product bottle
CTA: Order Now
```

**Matched landing page (Dads + Can't keep up with kids):**
```
Headline: Dads: Stop Getting Winded Playing With Your Kids
Subhead: Your beer belly isn't just about looks—it's crushing your energy and cardiovascular capacity. Target the hormonal cause without tanking your strength.
Hero: Video of dad playing soccer with son
CTA: Get Your Energy Back - 50% Off
Testimonials: "I can finally play full-court basketball with my kids again" - Mike, dad of 3
```

**Step 3: Set up URL parameters for tracking**

```
Landing Page A (Generic): yoursite.com/beer-belly
Landing Page B (Dads-Kids): yoursite.com/beer-belly?concept=dads-kids
Landing Page C (Lifters-Wife): yoursite.com/beer-belly?concept=lifters-wife
```

**Step 4: Update ads to point to matched landing pages**

Go into Ads Manager:
- All "Dads + Kids" ads → point to Landing Page B
- All "Lifters + Wife" ads → point to Landing Page C
- Everything else → Landing Page A (generic)

**Output:** 2-3 concept-matched landing pages live and connected to ads

---

### **Step 4.3: Test and Optimize Landing Pages**

**What it is:** Run A/B tests to validate that concept-matched pages actually convert better.

**Testing setup:**

**Week 1-2: Baseline**
- Run all ads to generic landing page
- Track conversion rate

**Week 3-4: Matched**
- Run ads to concept-matched landing pages
- Track conversion rate

**Metrics to compare:**
- Landing page conversion rate (purchases / visitors)
- Overall ROAS
- CPA

**Expected lift:**
- Well-matched landing pages typically improve conversion rate by 15-40%
- Example: If generic LP converts at 3%, matched LP might convert at 4-5%

**Optimization tips:**
- Test different headlines
- Test different hero images/videos
- Test CTA copy
- Test page length (short vs. long)
- Use heatmaps (Hotjar, Clarity) to see where people drop off

**Output:** Validated concept-matched landing pages with measurable lift

